column2: Testing done by DNR Mary Witt- Carol Alcole.  Sunny- breezy- DO: no oxygen 4 ft from bottom- 9.2 mg/l temp 16.46- 7 meters. 8.4c.
Rained hard yesterday AM- today cloudy- very humid- people on lake for holiday weekend- fishing- swimming
Some clouds and haze- light waves- heavy rain on 8/15 (3")
Sunny- waves from jet boats- low level
Clouds- light breeze- water very clear.
Sunny- some clouds- brisk wind.  Hard to hold anchor in solo canoe.
Hot- humid (extended period).  Overcast- hazy.  Breeze + choppy.   greater than 4" recent rain.
Partly cloudy- calm- nice day.  Some suspended green particles.
Mostly sunny- cool- calm- pleasant.  Some suspended matter.
Sunny- calm- pleasant.  48 F (after 3 late Oct. big blows).
beautiful day- sunny- no wind- 70's- water level high
3 days if rain. Humid. Haze. No wind. Lake high. Very dark day.     ICE OUT 4/14/02
Tough testing day. Hazy (smoke from Canadian fires)- humid- very dark- light breeze. 2 weeks hot and dry. Water great!  Nit L- Alk 80- Phos 0.8.
Glorious day. 62 F. NW wind. Bright sun. Choppy waves.

column1: Small suspended particles. Cold front with 2.5" rain passed through within 24 hours. Very good quality for August. Dragged anchor in solo canoe.

column2: Dark day. Light rain- lake high from recent rains. Green suspended particles
Clear- sunny- cold (29 F). No winds. Water high. Some small particles. Mostly clear. Lake edged with green/blue scum residue.
Clear- sunny- no wind. Water level high (but down from

column1: extremely high levels after heavy rains two weeks earlier---which

column2: Cloudy- overcast- light breeze. Some suspended

column1: material. Water plants emerging. Dark. Rain started. (Great timing.)

column2: Warm- humid- light breeze- overcast. Water excellent.
Cloudy- low ceiling- recent small thunderstorms- lake

column1: low- water clear- no boats- no wind

column2: beautiful day- cool (56 F)- after hot- dry- humid

column1: weeks- sunny- no clouds- light breeze- no boats- water level low.

column2: Cloudy- rain coming. Breeze.  Choppy waves. Lost plastic temp bucket. Probe pulled out.
Overcast- almost foggy.  Storms approaching.  No rains for several weeks.  Dry conditions.  Water level trending down.  Surface chop.
Overcast- some sun- cool- no wind. June cool and wet. No boats except two very curious muskie fishermen who wanted to see everything so we had a seminar at deep hole. Water plants emerging.
Hazy (western fires )- calm- ony boat on the lake.
Very cool (c. 50 F)- low clouds following light rain and mist; cool/wet summer; no suspended matter (unusual for August); moderate wind.
Raw and wild day. 34 F. Rain/snow- strong winds- waves- overcast. Musky action on lake. Otters out- too.
Missed spring test.  Beautiful- clear and sunny.  No wind.
Glorious day; 60s F at collection time; clear- sunny- light wind; no other boats; following hot- humid conditions; lake low and green.
Nice day- 70s after first rain in weeks.  Brisk wind.  Some waves.  A few clouds.  Lake low and green.
Cold- wet- rain.  Very dark day.  Windy.  Last test.  Tough conditions.  No choice.  Overseas past month.  Much rain.
First reading of the year.  Water clear in shallow water.  Bright sunshine.  Ducks and geese on lake.
Sun- hot- strong wind. Record heat in 90s. Rain the previous night.
Sun- brisk wind- dry period- nobody on the lake. My dog barked at the Secchi.
Record heat. 105 F in Hayward. Water low but good quality. Secchi only for Dip In. First time to use

column1: Secchi from a kayak. No problem. Sun and brisk wind. Heat should be mentioned again.

column2: Lake low- even after heavy rain previous night- after long hot- dry period. Very hot days. Little activity on lake. Sunny with brisks winds. Storms predicted.
Dark- misty- low light- and still. One other boat on lake. Water level up after dry- hot spell.
Raining- dark and still.  Perfect.  Two musky fishermen stopped by.  Caffrey the dog helped too.
Cool- windy- cloudy.  Very dry spring.  Recent rain.  Level remains low.  Late start for testing.  Boat motor repairs.

Bright- sunny- completely clear. Dead calm. No wind. Lake low. Record (for me) Secchi depth Rain needed. Caffrey- the Cairn terrier- helped. The "July test" will be the first week in August. Headed to Alaska.
Gone most of the summer. Alaska. Therefore missed July testing. By all accounts- it was hot and dry. Lake very low- aquatic plants in abundance. Outboard gas line broken- so canoe was used.

Lower Clam has made a wonderful come back- with recent rains- following a hot- dry summer. Lake high and clear. Sunny- light winds from SW and blue sky. 4 boats out (musky)- 2 came over to visit. Used a canoe with help from son- Chris- and Caffrey- the Cairn terrier.
Several attempts to test from canoe prevented by winds. Overcast- hazy- no wind- following much rain.
Little rain in August. Quiet Labor Day weekend. Clear- sunny- windy. QA tests too.
Sunny- cool- light wind. 2 boats with musky fishermen came by- curious.
Beautiful day- cool morning- light wind- clear- sunny- no clouds.  2 boats on the lake- 1 elk- 1 osprey.
Mostly sunny- moderate wind; outboard did not start- used solo canoe.

column1: No other boats on the lake. Recent rain.

column2: Mostly sunny day- a few clouds- light wind. No other boats. Recent rain. Cool- dry July and early August.
Last test for 2009. "Early" because I will be overseas until November. Fair- sunny day with light wind and a few clouds. No other boats. Lake clear and low after 3 weeks with no rain.

column1: clear- sunny day with light wind and a few high clouds. Rain needed. Many fishing boats. Holiday weekend. DEF

column2: The "June" test was late this year. DEF was overseas part of the month. Then- EWF had surgery (all is well) so Lower Clam was not visited for more than 3 weeks. Clear- sunny- windy with waves. 7-8" of rain during the past 3 weeks. Lake level high. No boats at the start of a holiday weekend.
Overcast- humid-still/ no wind. Significant rains in July. No boats on lake.

Clear- sunny- strong winds from the south and big waves. One fishing boat on the lake. Good year for rain; lake level high. Water plants abundant. Clear- sunny- strong winds from the south and big waves. One fishing boat on the lake. Good year for rain; lake level high. Water plants abundant.
Last test of the year.  Substantial rains again in September.  Some precipitation (snow or ice!).  30's.  No boats.

Ice out late this year- after a long winter- on 04/21/2011; dark and overcast. Still. No wind. One fishing boat. People were curious. Ice out late this year- after a long winter- on 04/21/2011; dark and overcast. Still. No wind. One fishing boat. People were curious.
Nice sunny day with a few fluffy clouds and brisk wind. Follows a week with significant rain. Lake high. One boat musky fishing on the lake.
Clear- still- sunny morning. No other boats. Storms approaching. Significant recent rains. Aquatic plants evident. DEF
Nice- sunny day with a few clouds. No wind. No boats. Probably final testing for the year. Western fly fishing trip in September then overseas until late October.
Mild winter. Early ice out in Mid-March. Clear- sunny day- after cold night. No wind. No other boats.
High water after heavy rains last week. Hot. Clear. Sunny. Slight wind. 2 fishing boats on the lake.
Pleasant 70s after weeks of hot- humid days. Outboard problems so canoe was used. Light anchor dragged in wind. 3 boats. 2 kayaks on the lake. High clouds. Moderate wind. Lake level down.
50 F. No wind at start. Later light breeze. Sun. No clouds. Mist rising. No other boats. Lake level slightly low.

late Spring. Ice out 05/11/2013. Heavy late snows in March- April and May. Heavy rains in recent weeks. Lake level the highest- I believe- in 20 years. Late start to testing. New boat has not arrived. Used a canoe. Dark day with storms approaching. Thunder storms the past two days. No wind. Mosquitos. No boats. Poor visibility. DEF Late Spring. Ice out on 05/11/2013. Late start to testing. New boat not available earlier. Heavy- late snows then heavy rains. Lake high. Dark day. No wind. Storms approaching.
Heavy rains in recent weeks. Cloudy- dark- poor visibility. Choppy waves. Difficult to anchor safely in solo canoe. Boat unavailable. No other boats on lake.
Sunny. No clouds. No wind. "Cool" 50 F overnight. Beautiful. Elk cow and calf at lakeshore earlier c. 5 am.
Sunny. Clear. Light wind. Almost 3 weeks of fair weather....70s. Cool overnights...40s and 50s. Little rain. Lake low and clear. 2 fishing boats.
Ice out 05/05/2014. Late start to testing. Cloudy- humid- windy. Heavy rains yesterday and the prior day. Lake high. Nobody else on the lake.
Late to start testing; ice out as of 05/05/2014; cloudy; humid; heavy rain (+1 inch) yesterday and the day before; windy
Nice Day; clear; no wind; no boats; cool in the 50s; perfect "fall-like" conditions; cool summer; good rain
Nice day...clear- no wind- no other boats. Cool 50s. Perfect "Fall like" conditions. It has been a cool summer with good rain amounts. DEF
Recent heavy rains; high water; busy - labor day weekend; partly cloudy; strong breeze
Recent heavy rains. High water. Lake very busy. Labor Day weekend. Partly cloudy. Strong breeze. Choppy.
Late start to testing.  Ice out 4/02! Much rain in spring.  Fair- sunny- 45 F overnight- good clarity- delightful day
Late start to testing. Ice out 04/02/2015. Much rain during early Spring. Fair. Sunny. 45 F overnight. Good clarity. Delightful day. DEF
Nice- sunny day after hot- humid period.  No boats- brisk winds- no clouds
Nice- sunny day after hot- humid period. No boats. Brisk winds. No clouds.
Partly cloudy. Recent substantial rains. Good wind. 10-15 mph. No boats. One eagle. Two loons. Noise from young osprey in pole top nest.
Recent rains- partly cloudy- good wind 10-15 mph- no boats- 1 eagle- 2 loons- noise from young osprey in pole nest

Late start to testing. Ice out between 04/05/2016 and 04/14/2016 while fly fishing in MT. Very high water after heavy rains. Sunny. Calm. No others boats. Tested from solo canoe. Lake too high to get boat off the lift.
Sunny. Light winds. High water after recent record rains. 2 fishing boats on Lower Clam.
Brisk winds dying after big front passed overnight. Mostly cloudy. No boats.

column1: NOTE: last test for 2016. Knee replacement on 9/12/16. DEF

column2: Very late start. Knee replacement. Overseas for one month. Much rain in early Spring. High water in June. Nice day. Sunny. Light wind.

column1: Ice out- I was told- on April 7.

column2: Almost high water level after 4" of rain a few days previous. Normal +. Partly cloudy. Brisk winds. Unusual direction from NE. No activity on Lower Clam.
Cloudy....dark- damp day after rain. Light wind. 2 musky boats on lake. Almost "high" water level.
Cloudy after fog. Heavy rains for 2 days. Moist still air. No other boats. Late Spring. Ice out on 05/04/2018. Very late!
Cloudy after fog. heavy rains for 2 days. Moist still air- no other boats. Late Spring.
Cloudy- gusty wind. Hot and humid- storms over night. Over 12" of rain in recent weeks.
Cloudy. Gusty winds. Hot. Humid. Heavy thunderstorms overnight. Much rain ( more than 12") in recent weeks. Interesting temperature profile. Colder than one month ago. No boats.
Clear sunny- no wind- no boats.
Clear. Sunny. No wind. No boats. Level down. Little recent rain. DEF
Cloud. Fog. 3" of rain yesterday. No boats. Calm winds. Clouds- fog- 3" of rain yesterday. No boats- calm wind.
Late to start to testing this year. Ice out on 04/22/2019. Long winter. High water in April and May.

column1: Sunny. Calm. Beautiful. One fishing boat on the lake.

column2: Nice morning. Partly cloudy. Calm. Two boats fishing. Music (loud) from youth camp over the PA. Why?

Wonderful day after overnight low of 42 F. Cool. Sunny. Clear. Calm. One fishing boat on the lake. Water level a little low after cool and dry spell. Water clarity good for this date. Relatively little aquatic plants for August. No report in September. Travel. Hopefully- there will be a Fall report in October.

Nice October day! Light winds in the morning. A few clouds. Snow coming soon. 1 musky boat on the lake. Late final test for the year to make up for missing September. We were gone for 5 weeks overseas on our #50 anniversary trip.
Late start to testing for obvious reasons. Ice out late on 04/19/2020. Long winter with much snow. Wet spring.

column1: Nice morning. Sunny. Moderate breeze. Two fishing boats on the lake. DEF

column2: Beautiful day. Calm. Sunny. Clear sky. No boats. No recent rains (1 week).  DEF
Cloudy. Muggy after c. 3" of recent rains. Calm gave way to very light breeze while on the water. One fishing boat on the lake. DEF

Pleasant Fall conditions after 5 cold nights + recent rains. Calm. Hazy and cloudy after fog lifted. One musky fishing boat. Last testing for a strange short season. Pulling boat to have a torn seam on the boat cover repaired.  Lake conditions have been very good this year. DEF
